---
description: Prisma and database rules
globs:
  - "prisma/**/*.prisma"
  - "src/lib/prisma.ts"
  - "src/**/*.ts"
  - "src/**/*.tsx"
---

Prisma rules:
- Use a single shared Prisma client pattern for the app
- Never instantiate PrismaClient repeatedly across files
- Keep database access on the server only
- Never import Prisma client into code that must run in the browser
- Prefer selecting only the fields needed instead of over-fetching
- Prefer clear relation names and explicit query shapes
- Keep schema naming and model naming consistent

Schema change rules:
- When changing Prisma schema, also consider:
  - whether a migration is needed
  - whether seed data must change
  - whether related Zod schemas or forms must change
  - whether pages/actions using that model need updates

Safety rules:
- Do not suggest exposing raw database errors to users
- Handle not-found and uniqueness errors cleanly
- Preserve data integrity and relation consistency